  "text": "When this decomposition is applied to the Ca 2+ imaging data (Fig. 4A) , we see that the eigenvalue spectrum has large values for the low-order modes and then rapidly falls to a smoothly decreasing function of index (Fig. 4B) ; theoretical expressions for the baseline distribution have been derived [CITATION_1] . The spatial and temporal modes show defined structure for the first 20 modes; beyond this the spatial modes appear increasingly \"grainy\" and the temporal modes appear as fast noise (Fig. 4D,E) .",
